## Why This Is Asked
Tests the ability to decompose a 128‑bit value into four 32‑bit lanes and re‑assemble them without branches.

## Key Concepts
- Lane extraction via masks and shifts
- 128‑bit as hi/lo pairs with 32‑bit lanes
- Branchless permutation and safe packing

## Code Example
```javascript
uint128 permute32x4_128(uint128 x) {
  uint32 A = (uint32)(x.hi >> 32);
  uint32 B = (uint32)(x.hi & 0xFFFFFFFF);
  uint32 C = (uint32)(x.lo >> 32);
  uint32 D = (uint32)(x.lo & 0xFFFFFFFF);
  uint128 y;
  y.hi = ((uint64_t)B << 32) | A;
  y.lo = ((uint64_t)D << 32) | C;
  return y;
}
```

