## Why This Is Asked
Endianness matters across 128-bit data paths; swapping bytes is a frequent low-level operation in serialization and network code.

## Key Concepts
- Endianness and cross-word byte reversal
- SWAR bit-twiddling for bswap64
- Handling 128-bit via hi/lo without 128-bit types

## Code Example
```c
static uint64_t swap64(uint64_t x) {
  x = ((x & 0x00FF00FF00FF00FFULL) << 8) | ((x >> 8) & 0x00FF00FF00FF00FFULL);
  x = ((x & 0x0000FFFF0000FFFFULL) << 16) | ((x >> 16) & 0x0000FFFF0000FFFFULL);
  x = (x << 32) | (x >> 32);
  return x;
}
void swapEndian128(uint64_t hi, uint64_t lo, uint64_t *out_hi, uint64_t *out_lo) {
  *out_hi = swap64(lo);
  *out_lo = swap64(hi);
}
```

