## Why This Is Asked
Tests mastery of non-trivial bit interleaving without loops, a common low-level optimization in graphics/encoding.

## Key Concepts
- Bit spreading (Morton order)
- Mask-and-shift interleaving
- 128-bit composition from two 64-bit halves

## Code Example
```c
// Pseudocode outline (no branches)
uint128 interleaveBits128(uint128 x){
  uint128 r;
  uint64_t lo = x.lo, hi = x.hi;
  uint64_t sLo = spreadBy2(lo); // using masks 0x5555.., 0x3333.., etc.
  uint64_t sHi = spreadBy2(hi);
  r.lo = sLo;
  r.hi = sHi << 1;
