## Why This Is Asked

- Checks 128-bit handling and branchless bit counting, a common crypto/DB pattern.
- Evaluates ability to compose primitives without loops.

## Key Concepts

- SWAR (SIMD Within A Register) popcount on 64-bit chunks
- Splitting 128-bit into hi/lo and aggregating results
- Constant-time, no branches

## Code Example

```javascript
unsigned int popcount64(uint64_t x) {
  x = x - ((x >> 1) & 0x5555555555555555ULL);
  x = (x & 0x3333333333333333ULL) + ((x >> 2) & 0x3333333333333333ULL);
  x = (x + (x >> 4)) & 0x0f0f0f0f0f0f0f0fULL;
  return (x * 0x0101010101010101ULL) >> 56;
}

unsigned int popcount128(uint128 x) {
  return popcount64(x.hi) + popcount64(x.lo);
}
```

