## Why This Is Asked

Tests ability to perform 128-bit two's complement negation and bitwise combination without loops.

## Key Concepts

- 128-bit arithmetic via hi/lo halves
- Two's complement negation with carry propagation
- Bitwise AND across full 128-bit value

## Code Example

```c
typedef struct { uint64_t hi; uint64_t lo; } uint128;

uint128 isolateLowestBit128(uint128 x){
  uint128 neg;
  neg.hi = ~x.hi;
  neg.lo = ~x.lo;
  // add 1 to lo, propagate carry
  neg.lo += 1;
  neg.hi += (neg.lo == 0);
  return (uint128){ .hi = x.hi & neg.hi, .lo = x.lo & neg.lo };
}
```

