## Why This Is Asked
Tests ability to extend classic bit-trick patterns to wider word sizes without branches, a common need in performance-critical systems.

## Key Concepts
- SWAR (SIMD Within A Register)
- 128-bit data layout with two 64-bit halves
- Branchless bit counting and aggregation

## Code Example
```javascript
typedef struct { uint64_t hi; uint64_t lo; } uint128;

static inline uint64_t popcount64(uint64_t x) {
  x = x - ((x >> 1) & 0x5555555555555555ULL);
  x = (x & 0x3333333333333333ULL) + ((x >> 2) & 0x3333333333333333ULL);
  x = (x + (x >> 4)) & 0x0f0f0f0f0f0f0f0fULL;
  return (x * 0x0101010101010101ULL) >> 56;
}

int popcount128(uint128 a) {
  return (int)(popcount64(a.hi) + popcount64(a.lo));
}
```

