## Why This Is Asked
Tests ability to design branchless bit tricks for palindrome detection on 64-bit values, a common bitboard problem.

## Key Concepts
- SWAR-based bit reversal
- Branchless boolean results
- Fixed-width masking patterns

## Code Example

```javascript
function reverse64(n) {
  n = ((n >> 1n) & 0x5555555555555555n) | ((n & 0x5555555555555555n) << 1n);
  n = ((n >> 2n) & 0x3333333333333333n) | ((n & 0x3333333333333333n) << 2n);
  n = ((n >> 4n) & 0x0F0F0F0F0F0F0F0Fn) | ((n & 0x0F0F0F0F0F0F0F0Fn) << 4n);
  n = ((n >> 8n) & 0x00FF00FF00FF00FFn) | ((n & 0x00FF00FF00FF00FFn) << 8n);
  n = ((n >> 16n) & 0x0000FFFF0000FFFFn) | ((n & 0x0000FFFF0000FFFFn) << 16n);
  n = (n >> 32n) | (n << 32n);
  return n;
}
function isPalindrome64(n) {
  return reverse64(n) === n;
}
```

## Why This Is Asked
