- How to adapt to larger coordinates or alternative word sizes?

## Why This Is Asked
Tests precise understanding of bit-rotation, modulo-64 behavior, and edge cases without branching.

## Key Concepts
- Rotation via (x << s) | (x >> (64 - s)) with s = n & 63
- Safe when s = 0 using masking (64 - s) & 63
- No loops or conditionals; only shifts and ORs

## Code Example
```javascript
// JavaScript BigInt version for 64-bit rotation
function rotl64(x, n) {
  const s = BigInt(n & 63);
  const MASK = 0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFn;
  return ((x << s) | (x >> ((64n - s) & 63n))) & MASK;
}
```

